name: BinarySwitch msg
Pushbullet Message
Click on this comment box, then click on the "Info" tab on the right -->
info:
If you *DON'T* want to use Push Bullet alerts, you can delete the line going from `BinarySwitch msg` to `Pushbullet Message`
If you just delete the line, you can later re-add if you decide to use Push Bullet alerts.

If you *DO* want to get Push Bullet alerts whenever a schedule fires, update the Push Bullet node. 
You'll need to click the "pencil" icon and enter in your Push Bullet API key.

You can get your Push Bullet API key from pushbullet.com - login and then click `Settings` on the left navigation.
You'll then see `Access Code` - copy that and paste it into the Push Bullet config.
